result.execSummary:
The defendant Herman Johnson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Intimidate Victim/Dissuade Reporting [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.44(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Defendant Herman Johnson in court with attorney Gregg H Novack.  Michael C Schindhelm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing Proceeded. Statements by parties and defendant.

AS TO COUNT 3
The court sentenced the defendant to 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive, with credit for 18 DAYS time served, straight time. Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 2 YEARS.

AS TO COUNT 4
The court sentenced the defendant to 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive, straight time. Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 2 YEARS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION
-Serve 25 DAYS in the House of Correction as Condition Time, STAYED pending review (per count).
-Batterers Intervention program.
-AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment.
-Absolute sobriety, random urine screens.
-Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent.
-No contact with victim, unless okay by the court or agent.
-No contact with firearms.
-Maintain/Obtain employment.
-Pay all court costs, fees, and surcharges including: supervision fees, and DV & DNA surcharges during period of probation, bail on deposit to apply balance to be returned to poster, failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

*Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief. 
*Court advised defendant of penalties for violation of NO CONTACT ORDER
*Court advised that under 48 USC Section 922(g)(9) the defendant is prohibited from possession of a firearm and/or ammunition after conviction of a misdemeanor crime of domestic violence.
*Court will allow for early termination of probation term if approved by agent and the court. 

Filed: 
-Pretrial Sentence Credit
-Notice of Right to Seek Post-Conviction Relief
-Memorandum of Conditions of Probation  Probation Review Hearing scheduled for August 15, 2014 at 01:30 pm.

AS TO COUNTS 1 & 2
Pursuant to plea negotiations, on a motion from the state the court ordered Count 1 & 2 Dismissed, But Read In for sentencing. 

AS TO COUNTS 3 & 4 AS AMENDED
Defendant changes plea(s) to NO CONTEST AS TO COUNT 4 AS AMENDED, and GUILTY AS TO COUNT 3. Defendant examined as to plea, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea(s).  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Court advised defendant of penalties for violation of NO CONTACT ORDER. Court advised that under 48 USC Section 922(g)(9) the defendant is prohibited from possession of a firearm and/or ammunition after conviction of a misdemeanor crime of domestic violence. Case passed to address court calendar.

AS TO COUNT 4
Pursuant to plea negotiations, on a motion of the State, Court ordered charge amended to Intimidate Victim (Misdemeanor), Domestic Abuse, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 940.44(1), 968.075(1)(a) a Class A Misdemeanor.
